festival.introText:
GoldCoast Oceanfest blends an intoxicating, eclectic and laid-back mix of quality music, exhilarating surf, beach sports and family-friendly fun.

If you could bottle a beachside festival and pour it out each year against the backdrop of a sun-drenched Atlantic, then the multi-award-winning GoldCoast Oceanfest might be just the brew to choose. It’s big enough to create a great party atmosphere, yet small enough to not be overwhelming.
 
Oceanfest blends a potentially intoxicating, eclectic and laid-back mix of quality music, exhilarating surf, action-packed sports, locally sourced food and family-friendly fun.

reviews.title: Review of GoldCoast Oceanfest 2022
reviews.body: it wasn't obvious it was going to finish so early, 9pm close it said, reef & dub club sets were ridiculously short. everything was closing by 8 very disappointed

reviews.title: Review of GoldCoast Oceanfest 2022

reviews.title: Review of GoldCoast Oceanfest 2022
reviews.body:
Oceanfest is a brilliant family friendly festival. Great range of music on the main stage and some awesome artists on the session stage!
Security was tight, but not overpowering, it all felt really safe. 
Roll on 2023!!

reviews.title: Review of GoldCoast Oceanfest 2022
reviews.body: so much fun, my voice now needs to recover

reviews.title: Review of GoldCoast Oceanfest 2022
reviews.body: event was great as always but felt sundays line up wasnt as good as saturday. although gentlemans dub club were brilliant. The rules on what you were aloud to take into the event seemed really strict this year. the email I got said no umbrellas, chairs, picnic baskets etc. were permitted to the event. turned up to find that there were people in the event with these. they are either band or there not. we had to go buy more stuff as we left everything at home as was under the impression certain things were not aloud. a little frustrating to say the least. but thanks again for a great wkend.

faqs.question: When is GoldCoast Oceanfest?
faqs.answer: GoldCoast Oceanfest itakes place from Friday 16th - Sunday 18th June 2023.

faqs.question: is there camping available at GoldCoast Oceanfest?
faqs.answer: no, there is not camping available at this event.

faqs.question: accessibility information
faqs.answer: • For Carer Ticket Password please email us on boxoffice@goldcoastoceanfest.co.uk we will confirm validity and issue a code to unlock the free ticket type.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Where is GoldCoast Oceanfest?
faqs.answer: GoldCoast Oceanfest is located in Croyde Bay, Norty Devon. the full address for croyde bay is Croyde, Braunton, EX33 1QB

faqs.question: How much are tickets for GoldCoast Oceanfest ?
faqs.answer:
GoldCoast offers children under 6 discounted entry, as part of a family, although they still must have a valid ticket, for £12.50 + booking fee. (A maximum of 2 per family)

GoldCoast offers under 18 (6-17 yr old) tickets from £60 +bf

GoldCoast offers 18+ tickets from £65 +bf

GoldCoast offers family tickets at a price of £270 +bf

faqs.question: Does GoldCoast Oceanfest have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer:
No, GoldCoast Oceanfest does not have any age restrictions

All under 16’s must be accompanied by a parent or guardian who is over 21 years old and this adult must remain on site throughout the weekend.

Age restrictions apply. Proof of age /ID may be required.

ID accepted onsite:

• Photo card driving licence issued by the DVLA

• Passport (photocopies not accepted)

• PASS: The National Proof of Age Standards Scheme

faqs.question: Do tickets for GoldCoast Oceanfest include camping?
can you re-enter the event in the evening if you leave?
faqs.answer: No re-entry to the arena after 6 pm. There will be no re-admission after 6 pm once the sporting events on the beach have finished for the day. This will only affect those leaving the arena and not people arriving for the first time.As an anti-counterfeit measure tickets are NOT sent out in the post. An eTicket will be sent to the email address you supply when buying your tickets. Simply print this email and bring it with you to the event.Please encourage your friends and family to get in quick – Oceanfest is spectacular value for money, considering it is a 3 day festival with over 20 live acts.
